uuuuttoouucchh -- Command

Touch a file to trigger UUCP poll
uuuuttoouucchh _s_y_s_t_e_m

The  command  uuuuttoouucchh creates  an  empty  control file  for  _s_y_s_t_e_m in  the
directory  /uussrr/ssppooooll/uuuuccpp/_s_y_s_t_e_m.  This  forces UUCP  to poll  _s_y_s_t_e_m when
uuuucciiccoo is called with the option -ssaallll. If the empty file for _s_y_s_t_e_m aready
exists, it is left alone.

There    are   three    types   of   files    in   the    spool   directory
/uussrr/ssppooooll/uuuuccpp/_s_y_s_t_e_m:

CC. Command file.

DD. Data file.

XX. Execute file.

_E_x_a_m_p_l_e
A typical usage is to put the following line into /uussrr/lliibb/ccrroonnttaabb:

    0 7 * * * /usr/lib/uucp/uutouch george

This forces  UUCP to schedule  a poll to  the remote system ggeeoorrggee  at 7 AM
local time.  The actual poll take place when uuuucciiccoo is started.

_F_i_l_e_s
/uussrr/ssppooooll/uuuuccpp/_s_i_t_e_n_a_m_e -- Directory for uucp work files

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o
ccoommmmaannddss, ccrroonn, uuuucciiccoo, UUUUCCPP
